	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary03.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>Wednesday 11</date>.</dateline>
				<p><name type="weather">The morning was dark and lowering,</name> &amp; the forenoon
					passed with <name type="weather">wind and rain.</name> This afternoon cleared
					brightly, &amp; though somewhat <name type="weather">windy, </name>it was
					beautiful I was notified that I was appointed judge advocate in a Court of
					Inquiry demanded by <persName key="Joseph Antoine Viguier De Monteil"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper061"
						>Lt Col Vignier de Monteil</persName> of the <orgName>New York
						53rd</orgName> commonly known as the <orgName>D'Epineuil Zouaves</orgName> ,
					on charges proffered against him by his <persName key="Lionel Jobert D'Epineuil"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper064"
						>Colonel D'Epineuil </persName>&amp; <persName key="Capt. W.W. Armstrong"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper183"
						>Cap W.W. Armstrong </persName>of the same Regt. The charges are
					unofficer-like conduct, getting drunk &amp; speaking disrespectfully of
						<persName key="Lionel Jobert D'Epineuil"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper064"
						>Col D'Epineuil</persName> - among the rest that he <persName>
						D'Epineuil</persName> had never seen service - never anything that a common
					sailor - also that he ate breakfast at the same <objectName type=" equpiment"
						>table</objectName> with his orderly. This Regiment dresses the same as the
					French imperial <orgName>Zouaves</orgName> - <objectName type="clothing">blue
						jacket trimmed with yellow</objectName>, <objectName type=" clothing">blue
						scarf</objectName> around the waist, s<objectName type="equipment">kyblue
						pants</objectName> - bagging down to the knees - <persName
						key="Thomas Grier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper076"
						>Tom Grier</persName> asked <pb
						facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary04.jpg"/>
					<fw><placeName key="Annapolis, MD"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl002"
							>Camp Union near Annapolist Md.</placeName>
						<date>December 11 Wednesday</date> continued 1861</fw></p>
				<p>one the other day whether he couldn't carry ten days rations in the seat of his
					pantaloons - <objectName type="equipment"> white leggings.</objectName>
					<persName>Tom </persName>took the notices of the Court of Inquiry over to
						<persName key="Lionel Jobert D'Epineuil"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper064"
						> D'Epineul</persName> - he saw his <persName>wife</persName>, a buxom
					French woman dressed in the full <objectName type="Clothing">Zouave
						costume</objectName>. </p>
				<p>We have a little black pup belonging to someone in the Regiment. He is called
					General, and is very playful. During the solemnity of the Dress parade, he got
					after the heels of <persName key="John Morris"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper057"
						>Lt. Morris</persName>, acting adjutant - then he treed the
						<persName>Colonel</persName>, and wound up with biting the heels of the
					Band, when they were beating off. The <persName>butler</persName> arrived this
					evening &amp; began by distributing a piece of <objectName type="other"
						>tobacco</objectName> to the boys. There was a grand rush - for they were
					nearly starved for it. It has caused great rejoicing, as they think it an end to
					their troubles, &amp; especially as they were notified at dress parade that the
					paymaster would be along soon. <persName key="Jacob G. Beaver"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						>Beaver</persName> went to town - to attend meeting I suppose.</p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
